----- EMAIL 2026-06-11T11:56:32.137230 -----
To: manager@bank.lk
Subject: New Circular 07/2024: Enhanced CDD and AML Controls

Dear Compliance Manager,

A new circular has been published.

Summary:
All licensed commercial banks are directed to strengthen their anti-money laundering and customer due diligence procedures with immediate effect. Banks shall conduct enhanced due diligence for all customer accounts where the aggregate monthly transaction value exceeds Rs. 5,000,000. Every bank must verify the source of funds and the beneficial ownership of such accounts before processing high-value transactions. Suspicious transaction reports shall be filed with the Financial Intelligence Unit within twenty-four hours of detection.

Please acknowledge by soon.

