----- EMAIL 2026-07-07T06:13:50.321341 -----
To: manager@bank.lk
Subject: New Circular 65/2025: Human Resource Policy on Remote Work

Dear Compliance Manager,

A new circular has been published.

Summary:
The Board of Directors of the Bank has approved the revised Human Resource Policy on Remote Work as per the attached Annexure I, with effect from 14th July 2025. All employees are strictly advised to adhere to the Human Resource policy with regard to their official duties and responsibilities. This Policy is formulated in line with the provisions of all relevant labour laws applicable for Bank of Ceylon. It is a set of guidelines and procedures that outline how the Bank will handle employees working remotely, either from home or other locations outside the office.

The Bank reserves the sole discretion to approve or refuse an application for Remote Work Facility. Agreement shall detail the terms attached to the remote work to be carried out by the employee, special benefits during remote work (if applicable), the supervision and other responsibilities of the Supervisor / Head of the Department. Remote Workers agree to be accessible and available to be contacted by the management, customers and other relevant stakeholders during the designated working hours.

The Remote Worker shall be governed by the Bank's existing Practices, Rules, Procedures or policies and Collective Agreements (as applicable) governing leave. The remote work location shall be considered as the location of work, to consider for leave, unless agreed otherwise in writing in the Remote Work Agreement. The Remote Worker must ensure that all equipment / tools / software supplied for Remote Working by the Management are exclusively used by the Remote Worker.

Employees will be required to participate at meetings as and when the Management requires them to do so, via any web-based conferencing tool. Matters of serious nature shall be escalated to the top management as per the Bank policies and practices. The Bank shall maintain an online database where it allows Remote Workers to record all hours worked, tasks in a manner an update on the work received, completed / attended to during the course of the day.

The Remote Worker shall indemnify the Bank against any and all claims, demands and liabilities, resulting from or arising in connection with, any injury to persons or damage to property. Failure to comply with this policy may result in disciplinary action being taken against the Remote Worker. All matters related to Remote Work will be administered, monitored and regulated by the Human Resources (HR) Department in consultation with the relevant line management.

Remote Work Approval Checklist: I Yes I No Name: Designation: Signature: Date: To be filled in by the Supervisor / Head of Department/Division: Received the duly completed Remote Work approval checklist. Work arrangement: I Permanent I Temporary I Occasional Duration: From (dd/mm/yyyy) To (dd-mm-yy-yyy) Reason for the request:    Workplace safety, electrical, fire safety, workstation equipment, and related materials.

The Remote Work Administrator must inspect the location and/or ensure all safety measures required are in order. Equipment used for Remote work are password protected. The Remote Worker must adhere towards the same during his employment under Remote Work conditions. Any deviation whatsoever from the guidelines set forth herein may amount to a misconduct on my part and that the Company can institute disciplinary action against me in this regard. I hereby certify that the above requirements have been satisfied in view of enabling remote work to be carried out as requested by me / designated by the Employer.

The Agreement shall commence and be effective from ……………………………. and shall be in force up to a date of termination of the agreement. The EMPLOYEE shall be entitled to commence Remote Work upon obtaining approval for the Remote Workstation. The standards to be maintained by the 'Approved Remote Work Location' shall be as follows. The Remote Worker shall be bound by the terms and conditions relating to maintaining confidentiality of all information concerning the Company.

Please acknowledge by 14 Jul 2026.

