----- EMAIL 2026-07-07T16:02:12.843019 -----
To: manager@bank.lk
Subject: New Circular 65/2025: Human Resource Policy on Remote Work

Dear Compliance Manager,

A new circular has been published.

Summary:
Overview:
Remote Work may be carried out either at the request of the Management or the prospective Remote Worker on mutual agreement, pursuant to granting of approval by the Management. Remote Workers agree to be accessible and available to be contacted by the management, customers and other relevant stakeholders during the designated working hours as detailed in the Remote Work Agreement. The Remote Worker shall be governed by the Bank's existing Practices, Rules, Procedures or policies and Collective Agreements (as applicable) governing leave. The Bank shall maintain an online database where it allows Remote Workers to record all hours worked, tasks in a manner an update on the work received, completed / attended to during the course of the day. Restricted access or confidential material shall not be taken out of the Primary worksite or accessed from the Remote work location unless approved in advance by the Remote Worker. The remote work location shall be considered as the location of work, to consider for leave, unless agreed otherwise in writing. The EMPLOYEE agrees to use the following items belonging to him/ her for the purposes of the Remotework: laptop, iPad, iPhone, iPad Pro, iPad Mini, Mac, Macbook Pro, Mac OS X and Macbook Air. Remote Worker agrees to be bound by the terms and conditions relating to maintaining confidentiality of all information concerning the businesses of the Company. Remote worker must ensure that all equipment / tools / software supplied by themanagement are exclusively used by him/her and for Remote Work purposes only.

Key Points:
- 4.1.2 A Remote Worker who has been designated by the Management to work remotely shall enter into a Remote Work Agreement (RWA) with the Bank, prior to commencing Remote Work.
- Such Agreement shall detail the terms attached to the remote work to be carried out by the employee, special benefits during remote work (if applicable), the supervision and other responsibilities of the Supervisor / Head of the Department.
- 4.3 Approved Remote Work Location: 4.3.1 The Remote Worker shall be eligible to work remotely from a location, nominated by the Remote Worker or the Management, as applicable, which has been granted prior approval of the Management.

Please acknowledge by 14 Jul 2026.

